{# ── What this library is ─────────────────────────────────────────────────── #}

<aside class="bmi-intro">
<strong>Standard reference ranges are designed to detect disease — not to optimize longevity.</strong> This library covers every biomarker through a different lens: what levels are associated with the longest, healthiest lives, what drives those levels up or down, and how to use that information to extend your healthspan. Each page includes longevity-optimized target ranges, a plain-English breakdown, and recommended ways to test.
</aside>

